Set oven rack about 6 inches from the heat source and preheat the oven's broiler. Line a rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil. Combine refried beans and salsa in a saucepan over medium heat; cook and stir until blended and heated through, about 5 minutes. Arrange tortilla chips on the baking sheet. Spoon refried bean mixture over chips. Sprinkle pepper Jack cheese, green bell pepper, and onion on top. Cook under the preheated broiler until cheese is melted, 3 to 5 minutes. Garnish with lettuce and olives.